# Folder structure — mandatory

Before creating or editing files, read `FOLDER_STRUCTURE.md` at the project root.

## Where to put new code

| What you're building | Where it goes |
|----------------------|---------------|
| Route entry (URL target) | `src/pages/<Area>Page.tsx` — thin wrapper only |
| Screen UI, charts, tables, forms | `src/features/<area>/` |
| Feature-only subcomponents | `src/features/<area>/components/` |
| Feature query/mutation hooks | `src/features/<area>/hooks/` |
| Shared button, card, table, input | `src/components/ui/` |
| Sidebar, TopBar, app shell | `src/components/layout/` |
| Route definitions | `src/routes/index.tsx` |
| Sidebar nav items | `src/config/navigation.ts` |
| Supabase/API functions | `src/api/` (no React imports) |
| Shared types | `src/types/` |
| Generic hooks | `src/hooks/` |

## Page pattern (required)

```tsx
// pages/DashboardPage.tsx — max ~5 lines
import { DashboardView } from '@/features/dashboard/DashboardView'
export function DashboardPage() {
  return <DashboardView />
}
```

## Feature folder per route

`dashboard` `/` · `users` `/users` · `courses` `/courses` · `financial` `/financial` · `chats` `/chats` · `reports` `/reports` · `account` `/account` · `help` `/help`

New sidebar route = update `navigation.ts` + `routes/` + `pages/` + `features/<name>/`.

## Do not

- Put business logic, API calls, or large JSX in `src/pages/`
- Put single-feature components in `src/components/ui/`
- Call Supabase from components — use `api/` + TanStack Query hooks
- Use `../../` imports — use `@/` alias

## Styling

Use design tokens: `bg-surface-page`, `bg-surface-sidebar`, `bg-primary-gradient`, `text-ink-heading`, `text-nav`. See `src/styles/variables.css` and `tailwind.config.ts`.
